562-4cdb-4a11-dc8a-f89133036dec"?></p><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="5f5451f7-eb4a-4de9-fe19-0d2264a12a93" text="—    inform all new arrivals about in .the organization of its internal gender equality policy;" timestamp="1668704451212"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="2474028d-cb6f-49ff-dad4-7be68f85d561" timestamp="1656533242829"?>—    promote the development and signing of gender <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2474028d-cb6f-49ff-dad4-7be68f85d561"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="2e74f138-33cc-4dc7-fdfb-4d0a6d0064fa" text="pledges within teams and organization" timestamp="1668704205226"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="040b59ec-fa97-45d6-c594-f9bfbc35e0a5" timestamp="1668704205226"?>commitment within top management<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="040b59ec-fa97-45d6-c594-f9bfbc35e0a5"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="f6c0460f-5144-49e0-fc67-1e25eaa6d472" text="s" timestamp="1668704441101"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="0e1b9ad8-3d35-495e-8dda-1b72b32d5830" timestamp="1668704447561"?> and all workforce<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="0e1b9ad8-3d35-495e-8dda-1b72b32d5830"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="2634fd9a-56e3-43bc-fe70-20a290c77bbf" timestamp="1656533242829"?>;</p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2634fd9a-56e3-43bc-fe70-20a290c77bbf"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="ed68143e-a4ef-49c5-dc73-b883ba7bd756" timestamp="1675420158385"?>—    inform all new arrivals about in the organization of its internal gender equality policy;</p><p>—  establish <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ed68143e-a4ef-49c5-dc73-b883ba7bd756"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="64afcda8-9b6d-4269-80dc-206a31c68009" text="[" timestamp="1675420159162"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="dfe0477e-1efc-4272-b370-bd245ee24192" timestamp="1668706037232"?>good practice how the organisation communicate and promote to all levels of the organisation<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="dfe0477e-1efc-4272-b370-bd245ee24192"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="62744512-0cc3-4dd9-b4ce-a93e15aba515" text="to implement - how " timestamp="1670339959098"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="4d6577eb-ffdf-40b2-f048-eec1e6ec2968" text="]" timestamp="1675420566040"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="7469ace7-5b00-47c0-db00-bcf2d498225e" timestamp="1668706037232"?></p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7469ace7-5b00-47c0-db00-bcf2d498225e"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="de4fa60b-f9cc-496d-d566-858ddb8c0c6e" timestamp="1656533242829"?>—    present its gender equality policy and the state of progress of the corresponding actions taken to all personnel once a year.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="de4fa60b-f9cc-496d-d566-858ddb8c0c6e"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="f7209b75-714c-4283-d7e0-77fd385387ad" timestamp="1656533242829"?>Organizations are encouraged to team up with specialized associations (see subclause 6.3.2) in order to raise awareness amongst internal stakeholders.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f7209b75-714c-4283-d7e0-77fd385387ad"?></p><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="ae94b664-ba98-45a0-dfa8-9e7439027d0f" text="P" timestamp="1666805717426"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="5191008" change-id="77d29948-31de-4780-d682-647033755f06" text="The organization of communal spaces and of the different areas in the school is another interesting example, such as the distribution of the youngest children in the school canteen, the room for afternoon naps, etc. This subject highlights the question of living in close proximity to one another and puts the notion of sharing at the very heart of the educational project. In this way, young children can discover values such as human dignity, freedom of choice, equality between girls and boys, solidarity, the spirit of justice and the rejection of discrimination.Theme-based posters explaining the rules governing society and, by extension, the rules that apply in the classroom. Young children take part in several written or oral exercises that simulate situations from daily life. These exercises highlight key notions of gender bias such as physical differences, timidity, mockery, etc.Very simple mini-debates are organized to discuss the sensitive aspects of living together, differences and equality, using card games that represent scenes from life in a group. Under the teacher’s supervision, the children discuss their perception of freedom, equality, and the absence of discrimination in their own words.Several examples can be given that demonstrate how learning to live together is of the utmost importance for children under six:The position of men and women at home, at work and in society in general is an essential subject that is at the very heart of all educational projects. It provides the means of learning about gender through family, the times they live in, traditions and the education system. In this way, young children can understand the importance of equality for all human beings, without distinction. They will gradually become able to describe different notions, such as violence and discrimination, by reflecting more and more objectively how to measure actions (insults, contempt, aggression, etc.). Teaching equality enables youngsters to understand that equality is not possible as long as any forms of discrimination and violence exist. Finally, as these children grow up, they will come to perceive equality as a social construct based on the responsibility of all.The teaching of gender equality starts at the very earliest age by taking concrete actions in schools that apply fundamental principles: respecting and knowing one another and accepting differences.Box 17 – Examples of tools to teach gender equality to young children" timestamp="1667311587687"?><p/></sec>